variables.name: IX_INDEXES_LENGTH
variables.comment:
* Number of int indexes.
     *
     * Can be 2 if there are only options.
     * Can be 7 or 8 if there are only options and a script reordering.
     * The loader treats any index>=indexes[IX_INDEXES_LENGTH] as 0.

variables.name: IX_OPTIONS
variables.comment:
* Bits 31..24: numericPrimary, for numeric collation
     *      23..16: fast Latin format version (0 = no fast Latin table)
     *      15.. 0: options bit set

variables.name: IX_JAMO_CE32S_START
variables.comment: Array offset to Jamo CE32s in ce32s[], or <0 if none.

variables.name: IX_REORDER_TABLE_OFFSET
variables.comment:
* Byte offset to uint8_t reorderTable[].
     * Empty table if <256 bytes (padding only).
     * Otherwise 256 bytes or more (with padding).

variables.name: IX_TRIE_OFFSET
variables.comment: Byte offset to the collation trie. Its length is a multiple of 8 bytes.

variables.name: IX_UNSAFE_BWD_OFFSET
variables.comment: Byte offset to char [] with serialized unsafeBackwardSet.

variables.name: IX_COMPRESSIBLE_BYTES_OFFSET
variables.comment:
* Byte offset to boolean compressibleBytes[].
     * Empty table if <256 bytes (padding only).
     * Otherwise 256 bytes or more (with padding).

methods.name: static void read(CollationTailoring base, ByteBuffer inBytes, CollationTailoring tailoring) throws IOException
